President Obama has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to the Closing Ceremony of the 2012 Olympic Summer Games in London. The delegation will be led by Susan E. Rice, the United States Permanent Representative to the United Nations. The delegation will attend athletic events, meet with U.S. athletes, and attend the Closing Ceremony. Other members of the delegation include Louis B. Susman, the United States Ambassador to the United Kingdom, Benjamin Rhodes, the Deputy National Security Advisor, Michelle Kwan, a member of the President's Council on Fitness, Sports and Nutrition and an Olympic figure skater, Reginald Love, a former Special Assistant and Personal Aide to the President, and Curtis Pride, a former Major League Baseball player and Gallaudet University Head Baseball Coach.